data.description: Welcome to this charming craftsman-style home in the sought-after Montreaux In Towne subdivision! The location is unbeatable! You'll be impressed by the spacious and well-maintained interior as soon as you step onto the charming front porch and enter the elegant 2-story foyer. The beautiful hardwood flooring and light, neutral color scheme create a warm and inviting atmosphere. A flex room is available for private and functional use, making it an ideal spot for teleworking. The kitchen/family room area is the heart of this stunning home! It's perfect for family gatherings, with the chef being able to interact while preparing meals. The eat-in kitchen has gas cooking, granite counters, rich, dark, gorgeous cabinetry, a double oven, a walk-in pantry, and a center island breakfast bar that will impress any cook. The spacious family room with a gas fireplace is perfect for snuggling up on chilly nights. For more formal gatherings, there's also a separate elegant dining room. This fantastic main level also includes a bedroom and full bath, providing ample space for your family to spread out and relax. You'll be impressed by the upstairs primary ensuite's spaciousness and cozy sitting area. The ensuite bath includes double vanities, a separate soaking tub, a large separate shower with a frameless glass enclosure, and even a water closet--not to mention the convenient linen closet nearby. The walk-in closet features his and her separation and leads directly to the laundry room. It's a clever design that you're sure to love! 3 additional spacious secondary bedrooms and a full bath round off this awesome level! You will love the decorative touches throughout! The lower level of the house has been partially renovated to include a spacious and inviting common area, perfect for spending quality time with family and friends. Additionally, there is a cozy bedroom and fully equipped bathroom, making it the ideal space for guests to unwind and relax. The possibilities for this area are endless, so let your imagination run wild! The outdoor space is equally impressive, with a lovely back deck that offers views of the secluded backyard - the perfect spot to kick back and enjoy some peace and quiet. Schedule your tour today! Tax Record reflects the correct square footage of 3,120. Find out RIGHT NOW how you may qualify for UP TO 2% below-market interest rates.
